# Global Engineering Rules — Agent Skills Pack
#
# This file is the Cursor adapter for the agent-skills engineering pack.
# It injects the always-on rules and provides navigation to the full pack.
#
# Source of truth: rules/code.md, role/role-standard.md

# === MANDATORY RULES (Always-On) ===

# META-RULE: Before finalizing any response or executing a command, you MUST
# explicitly verify your action against rules/code.md. If any step violates
# a rule, halt and ask the user for permission.

# Commit & Publish Safety
- Do NOT create a commit unless the user explicitly confirms that specific commit action.
- Do NOT push commits, create tags, or publish releases unless the user explicitly confirms.
- Ensure all code changes pass local linters, unit tests, and build checks before creating a commit.

# Code Standards
- Repo-local rules override these defaults when they are explicitly present.
- Prefer repo-local standards, templates, and workflows when they exist.
- Do not invent repository conventions, paths, branching models, or release rules not present in the active codebase.

# Wording & Metadata
- Do not mention agents, AI workflow, review labels, severity labels, task trackers, or other internal process metadata in commit messages, changelog text, release notes, or other user-visible change notes.
- Do not expose secrets, credentials, tokens, private keys, or sensitive internal values in commits, comments, changelogs, release notes, or other user-visible artifacts.

# Code Comments
- Prefer no comment over comments that merely restate the code.
- Keep code comments implementation-focused and useful.
- Keep each code comment within 3 lines unless a longer comment is required for doc comments, file headers, or tooling directives.

# === ROLE SYSTEM ===
#
# When the user assigns a Role, read:
#   1. role/role-standard.md (mandatory base standard)
#   2. role/<role-name>.md (specific role)
#
# Follow SKILL TOOLBOX LOCK: Only use Primary Skills from your role's Skill Toolbox.
# Follow BOUNDARY LOCK: Decline tasks outside your role's responsibilities.
#
# Available roles: role/README.md

# === SKILLS ===
#
# Organized by taxonomy under skills/:
#   skills/foundation/   — commit, review, test, navigate, troubleshoot
#   skills/backend/      — API, events, integrations, scaffolding
#   skills/frontend/     — UI components, pages, API client, testing
#   skills/platform/     — deployment, runtime debug, telemetry
#   skills/security-data/ — secrets, database, security audit
#   skills/documentation/ — technical docs, tech radar
#
# Each skill has a SKILL.md. Read it fully before executing.
# Skill index: skills/README.md

# === WORKFLOWS ===
#
# When executing a workflow:
#   1. Output a markdown checklist [ ] for ALL steps.
#   2. Process only ONE step at a time, mark [x], explain result.
#   3. Respect the Role: tag on each step.
#
# Available workflows: workflows/README.md
